; meeting-companion.form — the satsang companion: listen, transcribe, hold context, learn when to speak.
;
; THE ASK (Urs): ship speech-to-text, animal-sound events, and music/podcast (now-playing) events into
; the mesh and the native Mac + Android apps, so we get a meeting transcript AND the agent can listen,
; build context, and offer a question/insight — as text and audio — on a click, when named, or after a
; long pause when it is confident; almost never at the beginning, learning its turn from invitations.
;
; THE SHAPE: the BODY (recognition + the speak/stay decision) is Form, already proven; everything else is
; CARRIER (carrier-last). This is Lane 10 of sensing-lanes.form, made concrete.
;
;   mic ─► WAV chunk ─► STT carrier ──► text ─► [utterance cell] ─┐
;     │   (ffmpeg/AVAudio)  (mlx-whisper / SFSpeech / SpeechRecognizer)   │
;     ├─► SoundAnalysis ──► (label conf) ─┐                               ├─► [conversation cell]
;     └─► declared-source ► (title 100) ──┴─► recognition-router.fk ──────┘   (SEQUENCE of utterances,
;        (now-playing: ask, don't guess)     (strongest reading wins / silence)   content-addressed)
;                                                                                       │
;                                              cell-sync.fk (offer→verify-by-re-address, consent)
;                                              + mesh-relay.fk (payload = the cell) ──► shared field
;                                              (shared-sensing.fk: many bodies, quorum, cross-ground)  │
;            context = [pause-length, my-topic-mentioned, insight-confidence] ◄── built from the field  │
;                                       │                                                               │
;                       turn-taking.fk (tt-speak?: INVITED → speak; else PAUSE + CONFIDENT) ◄───────────┘
;                          │  invited interns "speak"; an unfilled pause interns "stay" (tt-learn)
;                stay (0) ─┴─ speak (1) ─► LLM composes the question/insight (satsang shapes) ─►
;                (silence,                    ┌─ text out (dashboard) ─┐
;                 whole)                      └─ audio out: AVSpeechSynthesizer (Mac) / TextToSpeech (Android)
;
; ── EXISTS (proven Form bodies + working carriers — the hard part is done) ──
;   - turn-taking.fk (→127, three-way) — the speak/stay gate, LEARNED from invitations. THE novel core.
;   - voiced.fk (→511, three-way) — the silence/speech gate that stops the STT hallucinating over silence.
;     A transcript is trusted only when the chunk is loud AND the STT is speech-confident (loudness from
;     mean dBFS; speechiness from 1−no_speech_prob). 0 silence (say/learn nothing) · 1 audible non-speech
;     (the oracle classifies + co-learning learns, but NO transcript) · 2 voiced speech (trust the words).
;   - recognition-router.fk (sound →127, sight →31) — fuse readings into one stream or honest silence.
;   - declared-source.fk (→127) — the cheap now-playing classifier (PREFER declared / SKIP the listener /
;     GROUND the inferred on the free declared label). Android MediaSessionManager carries it; on Mac the
;     inferred ShazamKit/SoundAnalysis path carries the load (iOS keeps now-playing private — honest).
;   - cell-sync.fk (→127) + mesh-relay.fk + shared-sensing.fk (→127) — content-addressed share, flood,
;     and the circle that makes many bodies one field.
;   - prose-as-recipe (WORD domain) — text → R_Block.SEQUENCE of word-cells, content-addressed.
;   - CARRIERS: satsang-voice (ffmpeg → mlx-whisper → rolling timestamped transcript; sound_classify.swift
;     = SoundAnalysis; shazam_song.swift), the eval-server + dashboard + per-frame kernel-eval, the
;     Android sense→stream→render loop, and the phone-native kernel cdylib (form_eval, symbol-verified).
;
; ── NEEDS BUILDING (carrier-work, named honestly) ──
;   1. THE UTTERANCE / CONVERSATION CELL — the ONE new body artifact: utterance = (speaker, timestamp,
;      text-as-prose-recipe); conversation = R_Block.SEQUENCE of utterances. Composes from primitives the
;      body already proves; content-addressing makes it a mesh payload for free (re-saying a line interns
;      to the same NodeID — dedup). The recipe that builds the turn-taking CONTEXT from it (pause from
;      timestamps, my-topic-mentioned from recent text) is the body link transcript → context → turn-taking.
;   2. AUDIO INTO /sense — add transcript / now-playing fields to the eval-server contract + a dashboard
;      panel (sensor-only today).
;   3. audio-grammar.fk — a runnable for the audio Language cell (only the .form skeleton + audio_emit
;      template exist; whisper/SoundAnalysis are the host-intrinsic stages, named honestly).
;   4. TTS carriers — AVSpeechSynthesizer (Mac) / TextToSpeech (Android), behind audio-grammar's audio_emit.
;   5. Android audio capture — RECORD_AUDIO permission + AudioRecord/SpeechRecognizer (manifest has only INTERNET).
;   6. cell-sync wire frames over socket/HTTP (BUILDABLE); peer discovery is the one genuinely-open edge.
;   7. Speaker diarization (optional, consent-gated) — gives the utterance its speaker field.
;
; ── THE MILESTONES ──
;   M0  the turn-taking decision body — SHIPPED (turn-taking.fk → 127).
;   M1  THE LIVE COMPANION LOOP — the BODY runs live, the transcript now has an honest gate:
;       experiments/satsang-voice/meeting_live.py. Per chunk: ffmpeg mic → loudness (mean dBFS) +
;       Whisper's no_speech_prob → voiced.fk gate-level (BODY: 0 silence / 1 audible non-speech / 2
;       voiced speech) → SoundAnalysis category + a cheap feature → nearest-shape (BODY) learns the
;       category (co-learning) → turn-taking.fk (BODY) decides speak/stay. VERIFIED live: the loop, the
;       learning (100% oracle agreement on audible chunks), and the speak/stay decision (correctly silent
;       on day one) all run on the real mic.
;       CORRECTED — the honest part: an earlier note here claimed a VERIFIED "real dialog" transcript. It
;       was not real. The mic was at the −56 dB noise floor (the room/playback audio wasn't reaching it)
;       and Whisper HALLUCINATED 222 words of fluent text — a documented STT failure on silence (its own
;       no_speech_prob was 0.81). Reporting that as a dialog was the overclaim. voiced.fk closes it: a
;       transcript is trusted ONLY when the chunk is genuinely loud AND the STT is speech-confident; silence
;       is reported as silence, never transcribed. When the source IS audible at the mic (loudness > floor)
;       the transcript flows — and a faint source still limits a tiny STT's accuracy, named honestly, not hidden.
;       PRIVACY: the transcript is processed + shown LOCALLY only, never sent, never committed (local compute
;       IS consent). (M1+M2 are both demonstrated here — the context [pause, named, words] feeds tt-speak?.)
;   M2  context from the transcript → turn-taking: build [pause, named, insight-confidence] from the
;       conversation cell, feed tt-speak?; the agent offers text when named/buttoned (still no autonomous voice).
;   M3  the mesh hop: the conversation cell rides cell-sync/mesh-relay to a second device (shared-sensing field).
;   M4  the agent's VOICE — SHIPPED + VERIFIED: experiments/satsang-voice/voice.py. turn-taking decides
;       WHEN; this arm is the WHAT + the sound: a LOCAL LLM (Ollama, no cloud — the dialog never leaves the
;       machine) composes ONE short grounded question/insight from the recent transcript, and `say` speaks
;       it as audio beside the text. Verified: composed "How do we ensure AI improvements stay aligned with
;       our goals?" from a sample context and spoke it to a 134KB audio file (to a file, not the room — the
;       agent speaks aloud only when invited). With M1+M4, the WHOLE loop runs: listen → transcribe → classify
;       → learn → hold the conversation → tt-speak? (WHEN) → compose (WHAT) → speak (text+audio) → learn the turn.
;   M5  Android audio in (RECORD_AUDIO + AudioRecord) + the now-playing declared-source; on-device form_eval.
;   M6  learned autonomous voice: tt-learn from real invocations; champion-challenger lowers the floor only
;       once it predicts the room's invitations — the companion finds its turn.
;
; WHAT GENUINELY NEEDS THE HUMAN: a mic-permission grant; felt verification in the room; and a real phone
; for on-device form_eval. Everything else (Mac mic, the cell shape, the dashboard, TTS-on-Mac) is
; verifiable on the dev Mac alone.
;
; KIN: turn-taking.form (the speak/stay heart) · recognition-router.form + declared-source.form (the
;   readings) · prose-as-recipe.form (the utterance/transcript cell) · cell-sync.fk + mesh-relay.fk +
;   shared-sensing.form (the mesh field) · audio-grammar.form (STT/TTS as the audio Language cell) ·
;   sensing-lanes.form (Lane 10 — this is that tool) · federated-slices.form (a learned turn-sense is a
;   shareable slice — circles teach each other when to listen).
;
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; THE 4TH-KERNEL REALIZATION (2026-06-11) — runs tomorrow
